# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Crazy Babo Bazar Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` (v2.0.1) using npm
- Package added to dependencies in `package.json`
- Lock file (`package-lock.json`) updated with new dependencies

### 2. Analytics Integration
Modified: `app/layout.tsx`
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component in the root layout, placed after `<CookieConsent />` and before the footer
- Component is now included on every page via the root layout

## Implementation Details

### Framework
Next.js 16.2.3 with App Router

### Installation Approach
Followed the official Vercel Analytics documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart):
- Used the Next.js App Router specific implementation
- Added the Analytics component to the root layout as recommended
- Placed the component at the application level to track all pages

### Code Placement
The `<Analytics />` component is strategically placed:
- Inside the `<body>` tag
- After the main content and cookie consent
- Before the footer section
- This ensures analytics tracking is initialized for all pages

## Testing Results

✅ **Build Verification**: Next.js build completed successfully (7.2s compile time)
✅ **Linting**: No new linting errors introduced in modified files
✅ **TypeScript**: Type checking passed (5.5s)
✅ **Static Generation**: All 20 pages generated successfully

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Analytics → Enable)
2. Verify tracking by checking the browser Network tab for `/_vercel/insights/*` requests
3. Monitor collected data in the Vercel Analytics dashboard

## Notes

- The Analytics component will only send data when deployed on Vercel
- Local development will not track analytics events
- The implementation follows Vercel's recommended best practices for Next.js App Router
- Existing code structure and formatting preserved
- All dependencies properly updated in lock file
